Continous Integration (CI):
---------------------------
	- CI is the process of automating the build and testing the code everytime
	  when a developer push the code to version control system
	- Developers write the code daily
	- Every time code is pushed, jenkins:
		build the code,
		runs tests,
		check if everything is working fine

	Sample Example:
	---------------
		- 5 developers are working
		- everyone pushes code to git
		- jenkins automatically:
			combines all code (integration)
			build it
			runs tests
		so no manual checking needed,
		CI = automatically merge + build + test code continuously


CI-Benefits:
------------
	- immediate bug detection
	- no integration step in the software depelopement lifecycle
	- a deployable system at any given point
	- record of evolution of the project